The paper develops a graph-theoretic framework for studying approximation algorithms for the Shortest Common Superstring (SCS) problem, which involves finding a shortest string containing each of a given collection of strings as a substring. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to sub-categories related to algorithms, data structures, combinatorics, and graph theory. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are all relevant sub-categories for this paper.
